# LeakSanitizer suppressions for the Criterion test runner.
#
# Criterion's runtime leaks a few small allocations from its own CLI/argument
# handling -- e.g. criterion_handle_args() strdup's the CRITERION_OUTPUTS spec
# and never frees it before exit. That is third-party code we do not control;
# suppressing leaks that originate in libcriterion keeps ASan flagging leaks in
# OUR modules while ignoring the framework's.
leak:libcriterion
leak:criterion_handle_args
